00:30:19.100 --> 00:30:22.640
Thank you very much. Our next speaker will be Marwan Fakhry,

514
00:30:23.380 --> 00:30:27.360
Dr. Marwan Fakhry at City of Hope National Medical Center, and

515
00:30:27.460 --> 00:30:31.350
he will be discussing AMG 355, a

516
00:30:31.480 --> 00:30:34.000
novel anti-CCR8

517
00:30:34.060 --> 00:30:35.540
antibody.

518
00:30:44.900 --> 00:30:46.620
You have to click start at the top.

519
00:30:48.560 --> 00:30:49.490
The top start?

520
00:30:49.500 --> 00:30:52.000
Scroll up to the top, right in the middle there by your name.

521
00:30:52.820 --> 00:30:53.600
No, with the mouse.

522
00:30:55.820 --> 00:30:56.260
All right.

523
00:30:57.560 --> 00:31:00.140
So I'm technology challenged.

524
00:31:01.300 --> 00:31:05.180
Good morning, everyone. It's a pleasure to be here, and thank you to

525
00:31:05.240 --> 00:31:06.360
the co-chairs

526
00:31:07.700 --> 00:31:08.400
and for the committee

527
00:31:09.600 --> 00:31:11.100
for selecting this

528
00:31:12.160 --> 00:31:13.540
abstract for presentation.

529
00:31:15.180 --> 00:31:19.080
So, on behalf of my co-authors and the lead author

530
00:31:19.140 --> 00:31:22.680
who could not make it today, I am presenting the initial

531
00:31:22.720 --> 00:31:26.220
results of a Phase I study of AMG 355,

532
00:31:26.800 --> 00:31:30.480
a novel anti-CCR8 antibody, as a single agent and in

533
00:31:30.560 --> 00:31:34.320
combination with pembrolizumab in patients with solid tumors.

534
00:31:36.780 --> 00:31:37.940
Here are my disclosures.

535
00:31:41.020 --> 00:31:43.300
AMG 355 targets

536
00:31:44.120 --> 00:31:48.060
CCR8, which is selectively enriched in tumors.

537
00:31:49.020 --> 00:31:52.620
We know that intratumor enrichment in CCR8-positive

538
00:31:52.740 --> 00:31:56.320
Tregs is associated with poor prognosis and that Tregs

539
00:31:57.420 --> 00:31:59.380
are associated with immunosuppression.

540
00:32:00.480 --> 00:32:04.260
The panel on the left shows the CCR8 expression in tumor

541
00:32:04.320 --> 00:32:04.840
versus

542
00:32:05.900 --> 00:32:09.490
blood and normal tissue, and you see that other Treg markers,

543
00:32:09.560 --> 00:32:13.120
canonical markers such as CCR4, CTLA4,

544
00:32:13.180 --> 00:32:16.860
CD25, and FoxP3, on the other hand, are expressed across

545
00:32:16.940 --> 00:32:18.400
normal tissue, blood, and tumor.

546
00:32:19.540 --> 00:32:23.080
AMG 355 is a Treg depleting monoclonal

547
00:32:23.140 --> 00:32:24.660
antibody engineered

548
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:28.419
for enhanced Fc gamma RIIIa binding.

549
00:32:30.160 --> 00:32:33.980
The afucosylated Fc fragment improves

550
00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:37.600
the NK cell bindings, resulting in more efficient

551
00:32:37.660 --> 00:32:40.840
ADCC and therefore Treg depletion.

552
00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:46.560
Here you see pre-clinical data showing in a CT26 model

553
00:32:46.680 --> 00:32:49.700
that the CCR8 depletion in blue

554
00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:55.020
with a CCR8 depleting antibody is associated with clinical activity, while

555
00:32:55.060 --> 00:32:57.780
CCR8 binding without depletion

556
00:32:58.780 --> 00:33:01.460
in red did not have any significant activity.

557
00:33:02.660 --> 00:33:06.560
CCR8 binding with a Treg

558
00:33:06.600 --> 00:33:10.460
depleting antibody through ADCC is associated with

559
00:33:10.740 --> 00:33:14.460
a decrease in CCR8-positive Tregs in the tumor,

560
00:33:15.140 --> 00:33:18.400
but no impact on the expression in spleen and lymph node.

561
00:33:19.540 --> 00:33:23.320
And on the right, you can see in an MC38 model

562
00:33:23.800 --> 00:33:26.960
that the combination with an anti-PD-1 and an

563
00:33:27.040 --> 00:33:30.920
anti-CCR8, specifically a Treg depleting

564
00:33:30.960 --> 00:33:34.930
anti-CCR8, is associated with robust clinical activity with

565
00:33:34.960 --> 00:33:38.100
nine out of ten CRs in an MC38 model.

566
00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:41.700
And this synergistic activity is the

567
00:33:41.740 --> 00:33:42.769
driver for the

568
00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:45.640
hypothesis

569
00:33:46.660 --> 00:33:48.820
for looking at the combination clinically.

570
00:33:52.560 --> 00:33:55.000
So in this Phase I clinical trial,

571
00:33:57.800 --> 00:34:01.760
AMG 355 was evaluated as a monotherapy

572
00:34:01.840 --> 00:34:04.180
or in combination with pembrolizumab.

573
00:34:05.360 --> 00:34:08.781
The top escalation plot shows the monotherapy

574
00:34:08.821 --> 00:34:12.740
escalation starting at a very low dose of 0.28 milligram

575
00:34:13.740 --> 00:34:17.460
all the way up to 700 milligram. It was given intravenously every three

576
00:34:17.580 --> 00:34:18.000
weeks.

577
00:34:19.120 --> 00:34:22.940
The study design was an accelerated escalation

578
00:34:23.020 --> 00:34:26.680
design, initially with one patient per cohort until we hit a Grade 2

579
00:34:26.700 --> 00:34:30.680
toxicity. And once a Grade 2 toxicity is noted, the escalation

580
00:34:30.761 --> 00:34:33.700
goes to three patients minimum per cohort.

581
00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:36.620
Backfill cohorts were also included

582
00:34:37.560 --> 00:34:41.540
starting cohort number six, and those cohorts had mandatory

583
00:34:41.700 --> 00:34:44.100
pre and Cycle 2 biopsies.

584
00:34:45.801 --> 00:34:49.620
On the combination arm, the escalation started at 70 milligrams for

585
00:34:49.700 --> 00:34:52.960
AMG 355, all the way up to 700 milligrams.

586
00:34:53.520 --> 00:34:55.761
To the right, you can see the patient demographics.

587
00:34:56.540 --> 00:35:00.500
Seventy-seven patients were enrolled on this study, 47 on the monotherapy

588
00:35:00.620 --> 00:35:02.220
arm, 30 on the combination.

589
00:35:03.200 --> 00:35:07.160
The histologies that were allowed were colorectal, gastric, non-small

590
00:35:07.220 --> 00:35:11.140
cell lung cancer, and melanoma, with only four patients with melanoma enrolled in

591
00:35:11.180 --> 00:35:14.800
this study. These patients were heavily pretreated with a median number

592
00:35:14.940 --> 00:35:17.840
of therapies of three lines of treatment.

593
00:35:18.600 --> 00:35:22.340
About 40% of patients on this study had prior PD-1 or PD-L1

594
00:35:22.380 --> 00:35:23.080
exposure.

595
00:35:24.400 --> 00:35:28.340
You can see that the CCR8 at baseline by immune positive

596
00:35:28.400 --> 00:35:32.240
score percentage was a median of 5.5

597
00:35:32.320 --> 00:35:35.220
on the monotherapy and four on the combination.

598
00:35:39.360 --> 00:35:43.080
Here we show the safety data. No dose-limiting toxicities were

599
00:35:43.120 --> 00:35:44.240
noted on this study.

600
00:35:45.680 --> 00:35:49.540
The tornado plots to the right show the treatment

601
00:35:49.580 --> 00:35:53.560
emergent adverse events and the treatment-related adverse events to

602
00:35:53.600 --> 00:35:56.980
the right of each plot. The top plot is for the monotherapy arm.

603
00:35:57.040 --> 00:35:59.160
The bottom plot is for the combination arm.

604
00:35:59.840 --> 00:36:03.380
Note that the agent was relatively safe with Grade 3

605
00:36:03.600 --> 00:36:07.520
treatment-related adverse event on the monotherapy arm limited to less than

606
00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:08.820
5% of patients.

607
00:36:09.720 --> 00:36:13.380
One patient with increased LFTs and one patient with diarrhea with Grade 3

608
00:36:13.460 --> 00:36:15.280
toxicities were noted in this cohort.

609
00:36:16.460 --> 00:36:20.440
On the bottom, you can see the tornado plot for the pembrolizumab plus AMG

610
00:36:20.580 --> 00:36:24.200
355.And you can see here that the

611
00:36:24.680 --> 00:36:28.400
more grade three toxicities were noted, but still only about 17% of

612
00:36:28.460 --> 00:36:30.280
patients had grade three toxicities.

613
00:36:31.080 --> 00:36:34.430
Again, those were mostly GI, such as amylase,

614
00:36:34.480 --> 00:36:35.160
lipase,

615
00:36:36.260 --> 00:36:40.200
and there was also lymphopenia, hyperglycemia, and hypoalbuminemia.

616
00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:45.260
Most of the toxicities related to AMG 355 on both arms

617
00:36:45.360 --> 00:36:49.160
were grade one and grade two infusion reactions, as you can see on the top of

618
00:36:49.200 --> 00:36:53.100
each tornado plot, and those were limited to the

619
00:36:53.140 --> 00:36:55.179
day one of cycle one.

620
00:36:57.500 --> 00:37:01.340
Here we show the pharmacokinetics, and I want to note here that

621
00:37:01.410 --> 00:37:04.840
this is a dose-normalized AUC. So if you see

622
00:37:05.140 --> 00:37:09.100
that the plot is the same across all dose level, it indicates

623
00:37:09.140 --> 00:37:12.920
that there is consistency in elimination and dose-related

624
00:37:12.980 --> 00:37:14.640
increase in pharmacokinetics.

625
00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:18.840
Now we move to the efficacy.

626
00:37:20.580 --> 00:37:24.360
Here you see three plots on three different

627
00:37:24.440 --> 00:37:28.320
rows. The first row is for the duration of treatment for

628
00:37:28.380 --> 00:37:31.040
each individual patient, the middle is for the

629
00:37:32.040 --> 00:37:36.020
waterfall plot for the target lesions efficacy, and the third is for

630
00:37:36.060 --> 00:37:38.720
the IPS score for CCR8 expression.

631
00:37:39.740 --> 00:37:43.520
To the left, the three plots show the monotherapy, and to the right, you can

632
00:37:43.540 --> 00:37:45.100
see the combination.

633
00:37:46.780 --> 00:37:50.580
On the monotherapy arm, we see one patient with a partial response.

634
00:37:50.680 --> 00:37:54.300
This is a patient with melanoma who had previously been treated with a PD-1

635
00:37:54.340 --> 00:37:58.200
CTLA-4 therapy with subsequent progression.

636
00:37:58.220 --> 00:38:01.440
This patient, as you can see, had a very durable response.

637
00:38:03.360 --> 00:38:07.320
Note that the stable disease rate on the monotherapy between 70 to

638
00:38:07.640 --> 00:38:11.560
700 milligrams was 19%. There's no strong

639
00:38:11.640 --> 00:38:13.440
correlation that we can say between

640
00:38:14.260 --> 00:38:18.160
the IPS score and response, but note that there was

641
00:38:18.220 --> 00:38:20.160
only one response in this situation.

642
00:38:20.630 --> 00:38:23.380
But we do not see a specific signal with SD either.

643
00:38:24.680 --> 00:38:27.740
On the combination arm, we have one patient with a complete

644
00:38:28.020 --> 00:38:31.839
response. This is a patient with gastric cancer who had

645
00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:33.340
prior nivolumab.

646
00:38:34.540 --> 00:38:38.340
The stable disease rate on the combination arm was 33%.

647
00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:47.080
Here we show the pharmacodynamics on the study

648
00:38:47.720 --> 00:38:49.460
with the CCRA depletion.

649
00:38:50.360 --> 00:38:52.440
To the left, you can see the

650
00:38:53.320 --> 00:38:57.020
monotherapy on the part A and the combination on part B.

651
00:38:57.920 --> 00:39:01.490
And at all dose levels from 70 milligrams to 700

652
00:39:01.520 --> 00:39:05.100
milligrams, you can see robust depletion in CCR8 positive

653
00:39:05.180 --> 00:39:08.740
cells. This applies both for the monotherapy and the combination

654
00:39:08.800 --> 00:39:12.640
arms. And the plot to the right shows the pool

655
00:39:12.720 --> 00:39:16.460
data for all patients who underwent biopsies on this study, with a

656
00:39:16.500 --> 00:39:20.320
robust number of patients undergoing a screening biopsy and a cycle two

657
00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:21.080
biopsy.

658
00:39:25.060 --> 00:39:28.620
Here we show the CCR8 over CD8 ratio with a similar

659
00:39:28.760 --> 00:39:32.720
pattern of reduction in the CCR8 over CD8 ratio, again

660
00:39:32.780 --> 00:39:35.320
suggesting modulation of the tumor microenvironment.

661
00:39:37.760 --> 00:39:41.500
This is an example of immunohistochemistry on a patient

662
00:39:41.600 --> 00:39:41.760
with

663
00:39:42.780 --> 00:39:46.530
melanoma involving the skin, lymph nodes, lung, pancreas, and

664
00:39:48.020 --> 00:39:51.660
with gastric metastases as well. This patient was treated with

665
00:39:51.720 --> 00:39:55.110
pembrolizumab for three years with the best response, with partial response with

666
00:39:55.180 --> 00:39:59.120
subsequent progression, and started AMG 355 monotherapy at 70

667
00:39:59.160 --> 00:40:03.060
milligram Q3 weeks at a partial response, and that's the patient I

668
00:40:03.080 --> 00:40:03.480
pointed

669
00:40:04.400 --> 00:40:07.900
to on the waterfall plots. You can see

670
00:40:07.960 --> 00:40:11.860
substantial reduction in CCR8 positive cells on

671
00:40:11.900 --> 00:40:14.120
cycle number two compared to cycle number one.

672
00:40:14.700 --> 00:40:18.440
On the other hand, subject number two is a patient with colorectal cancer with

673
00:40:18.520 --> 00:40:22.340
also substantial reduction in CCR8 positivity on cycle

674
00:40:22.400 --> 00:40:23.920
number two compared to screening.

675
00:40:24.340 --> 00:40:28.080
However, this patient, who had previously progressed after FOLFIRINOX and

676
00:40:28.120 --> 00:40:31.560
FOLFIRI, had progression on the first imaging after

677
00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:34.660
initiation of AMG 355 with progressive disease.

678
00:40:36.980 --> 00:40:40.420
So to conclude, AMG 355 was safe

679
00:40:40.879 --> 00:40:44.490
and tolerable at doses up to 700 milligrams, but

680
00:40:44.580 --> 00:40:48.300
clinical activity as a single agent or in combination with pembrolizumab

681
00:40:48.660 --> 00:40:49.340
was limited.

682
00:40:50.250 --> 00:40:53.820
Paired biopsy data supports pharmacodynamic activity of AMG

683
00:40:53.960 --> 00:40:57.690
355 with a decrease in CCR8 seen, as well as a

684
00:40:57.700 --> 00:41:01.300
decrease in CCR8 over CD8 ratio in most

685
00:41:01.400 --> 00:41:04.140
subjects on treatment, suggesting modulation of the tumor

686
00:41:04.240 --> 00:41:06.820
microenvironment on this study.

687
00:41:07.960 --> 00:41:11.760
Additional tissue-based multiomics spatial analyses are planned in a

688
00:41:11.820 --> 00:41:15.080
subset of paired biopsies to further characterize changes in the tumor

689
00:41:15.160 --> 00:41:18.480
microenvironment, including immune cell profiles. Thank you.

690
00:41:20.360 --> 00:41:23.910
I would just like to thank the patients, their families, and

691
00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:25.740
caregivers, and all investigators.

692
00:41:26.880 --> 00:41:30.560
Special thanks to the AMG 355 team across Amgen Research and

